The paper deals with distributed protocols for finding similar vectors in a large dataset, which is a problem in distributed computing and data structures. The paper also makes use of graph-theoretic concepts and combinatorial optimization, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses distance correlations and information theory, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper's focus on similarity search and machine learning also suggests the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
